<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA0FFFEF855AB308284FB93" box="[544,737,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
A. a. 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA0FFFEF82BAB308284FB93" authorityName="Ortmann" authorityYear="1893" box="[606,737,1118,1143]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Acetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanus">americanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is captured preferably in lower depths and high temperatures (23.5‒28.5°C) (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA0FFFEFB3DABEF8246FB7F" author="Simoes, S. M. &amp; Castilho, A. L. &amp; Fransozo, A. &amp; Negreiros-Fransozo, M. L. &amp; Costa, R. C." box="[328,547,1153,1179]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="753 - 759" refId="ref78664" refString="Simoes, S. M., Castilho, A. L., Fransozo, A., Negreiros-Fransozo, M. L. &amp; Costa, R. C. (2013) Distribution related to temperature and salinity of the shrimps Acetes americanus and Peisos petrunkevitchi (Crustacea: Sergestoidea) in the south-eastern Brazilian littoral zone. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 93 (3), 753 - 759. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315412000902" type="journal article" year="2013">
Simões 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA0FFFEFBD1ABEC81BBFB7F" box="[420,478,1153,1179]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Although it may be captured incidentally as bycatch with other shrimps, and the consumption of specimens of the same genus occurs in the northern 
<collectingCountry id="14C6039BFFA0FFFEF9C5ABCB8392FB5B" box="[944,1015,1189,1215]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, these were not considered significant threats to the species (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA0FFFEFBE1ABA782F1FB00" author="Costa, R. C. &amp; Simoes, S. M." box="[404,660,1225,1252]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="366 - 376" refId="ref59408" refString="Costa, R. C. &amp; Simoes, S. M. (2016) Avaliacao dos camaroes sicionideos (Decapoda: Sicyoniidae). Chapter 27, 366 - 376. In: Pinheiro, M. A. A. &amp; Boos, H. (Org.), Livro Vermelho dos Crustaceos do Brasil: Avaliacao 2010 - 2014. Porto Alegre, RS, Sociedade Brasileira de Carcinologia - SBC, 466 pp." type="book chapter" year="2016">Costa &amp; Simões 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The taxonomic status of this genus has been under debate for long time and some subspecies are still considered valid as 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA0FFFEF97FAB808381FAE3" box="[778,996,1261,1288]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA0FFFEF97FAB808336FAEC" authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1830" box="[778,851,1262,1288]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Acetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Acetes</taxonomicName>
a. carolinae
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA0FFFEFE6AAB808484FAE3" box="[1055,1249,1262,1288]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
A. a. 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA0FFFEFE2BAB808484FAE3" authorityName="Ortmann" authorityYear="1893" box="[1118,1249,1262,1287]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Acetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanus">americanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA0FFFEFE84AB8385F2FAE3" author="Holthuis, L. B." box="[1265,1431,1261,1287]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="1104 - 1113" refId="ref64425" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1948) Notes on some Crustacea Decapoda Natantia from Surinam. Proceedings Koninklijke Nederlandsche Akademie van Wetenschappen, 51, 1104 - 1113." type="journal article" year="1948">Holthuis 1948</bibRefCitation>
; WoRMS 2022). A molecular study in progress by our team (Simões 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA0FFFEF9B5AA7C8399FACF" box="[960,1020,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
in progress) will sheds light in the taxonomic status and the identity of 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA0FFFEF858AA58828EFAAB" box="[557,747,1334,1360]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
A. a. 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA0FFFEF81DAA58828EFAAB" authorityName="Ortmann" authorityYear="1893" box="[616,747,1334,1359]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Acetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="americanus">americanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, as well as its relationship with other congeners from western Atlantic. Sequences accession number (GenBank): CCDB 4939—16S (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFA0FFFEF9CCAA37845CFA90" box="[953,1081,1369,1396]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KX196538" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">KX196538</accessionNumber>
), COI (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FFA0FFFEFEF8AA37856EFA90" box="[1165,1291,1369,1396]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/KX196595" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">KX196595</accessionNumber>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA0FFFEFF54AA378176FA73" author="Mantelatto, F. L. &amp; Terossi, M. &amp; Negri, M. &amp; Buranelli, R. C. &amp; Robles, R. &amp; Magalhaes, T. &amp; Tamburus, A. F. &amp; Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J." pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="805 - 815" refId="ref68637" refString="Mantelatto, F. L., Terossi, M., Negri, M., Buranelli, R. C., Robles, R., Magalhaes, T., Tamburus, A. F., Rossi, N. &amp; Miyazaki, M. J. (2018) DNA sequence database as a tool to identify decapod crustaceans on the Sao Paulo coastline. Mitochondrial DNA Part A: DNA Mapping, Sequencing and Analysis, 29 (5), 805 - 815. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 24701394.2017.1365848" type="journal article" year="2018">
Mantelatto 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA0FFFEFAE2AA1080AAFA73" box="[151,207,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFFA0FFFEFAE2AA878240F9E7" blockId="20.[151,549,1513,1539]" box="[151,549,1513,1539]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA0FFFEFAE2AA878240F9E7" bold="true" box="[151,549,1513,1539]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="ABD13888FFA0FFFEFA9BAA878240F9E7" authority="Burkenroad, 1945" authorityName="Burkenroad" authorityYear="1945" box="[238,549,1513,1539]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sergestidae" genus="Peisos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FFA0FFFEFA9BAA87815EF9E7" bold="true" box="[238,315,1513,1539]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Peisos</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFFA0FFFEFB37AA878240F9E7" author="Burkenroad, M. D." box="[322,549,1513,1539]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" pagination="553 - 591" refId="ref55677" refString="Burkenroad, M. D. (1945) A new sergestid shrimp (Peisos petrunkevitchii, n. gen., n. sp.), with remarks on its relationships. Transactions of the Connecticut Academy of Arts and Sciences, 36, 553 - 591." type="journal article" year="1945">Burkenroad, 1945</bibRefCitation>
